{{Use New Zealand English|date=October 2016}}

The '''Dunedin Fringe Festival''', or '''Dunedin Fringe''', is an 11-day [[fringe theatre]] festival held each March in [[Dunedin]], [[New Zealand]]. The first Dunedin Fringe was in the year 2000.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dunedinfringe.nz/about/ |title=About Dunedin Fringe |website=Dunedin Fringe |access-date=12 October 2016}}</ref>

In addition to theatrical performances, the festival hosts dancers and live music.<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.scoop.co.nz/stories/CU1412/S00390/dunedin-fringe-reveals-first-programme-announcments-for-2015.htm |title=Dunedin Fringe Reveals First Programme Announcements for 2015 |date=19 December 2014 |publisher=''[[Scoop (website)|Scoop]]'' |location=Dunedin |access-date=12 October 2016}}</ref> In 2016, artists produced 55 shows.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.odt.co.nz/news/dunedin/fringe-director-thrilled-festival |title=Fringe director thrilled with festival |last=McAvinue |first=Shawn |date=17 March 2016 |website=[[Otago Daily Times]] |access-date=12 October 2016}}</ref> The festival is open-access, which means that anyone who registers may perform.

The venues are in and around [[The Octagon, Dunedin|the Octagon]], the city centre of Dunedin. Among these are [[Allen Hall (University of Otago)|Allen Hall]] at the [[University of Otago]]; The [[Fortune Theatre, Dunedin|Fortune Theatre]];<ref>{{cite book |title=Fodor's Essential New Zealand |editor-last=Cameron |editor-first=Róisín |editor2-last=Jabado |editor2-first=Salwa |editor3-last=Minford |editor3-first=Teddy |page=1072 |publisher=Fodor's Travel |isbn=978-0-8041-4364-6}}</ref> the Octagon Athenaeum; and Dog With Two Tails, a nearby café and bar.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dunedinfringe.nz/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Venue-List-2017.pdf |format=PDF |title=Dunedin Fringe Festival 2017 Venue List |date=11 August 2016 |website=Dunedin Fringe |access-date=12 October 2016}}</ref>

